1:192.name: Configuration=Filled, State=focused, Show Icon=False
1:192.description:
Filled buttons are high-emphasis buttons.
They have the most visual impact after the FAB, and should be used for important, final actions that complete a flow, like "Save", "Join now", or "Confirm".

1:55.name: Configuration=Tonal, State=hovered, Show Icon=False
1:55.description:
Tonal buttons are medium-emphasis buttons.
They are an alternative middle ground between filled and outlined buttons. Theyre useful in contexts where a lower-priority button requires slightly more emphasis than an outline would give, such as "Next" in an onboarding flow.

1:25.name: [m3:button] Button
1:25.description: Buttons communicate actions that users can take. They are typically placed throughout your UI, in places like Dialogs, Modal windows, Forms, Cards and Toolbars
